foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Regarding “Number of Requests Pending as of Start of Fiscal Year”: Although DOI indicated in its FY 2008 Annual Report that there were 905 requests pending at the end of the fiscal year, the figure denoted in this chart is correct. The difference is attributed to the following: 1) in some instances the bureau/office did not show requests that were in fact completed in FY 2008 as completed in the EFTS until after the FY 2008 report was finalized; 2) there were some discrepancies in accounting; 3) requests opened in the EFTS solely for the purpose of electronically assigning action to a Regional or Field Office were not counted in prior reports, but are counted here and will be included in future reports; and 4) some bureaus/offices were not using an electronic tracking system and their numbers reported were inaccurate.
